<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
When I was 19th I went to Lake of Ill Omen<P>I would do this...<P>Cast Disease to pull..<P>Run back to my "fighting spot" and cast slow<P>After the mob's inital round of attacks I would then cast my poison spell..<P>Then melee till it died...<P>If it was beating me badly then I would root and back off to either heal /dd or apply another dot...<P>The reason I did the disease to pull was<BR>2 fold...1) "replaces" the pet's damage at lower levels...2) It has a slower casting time than slow, so it's easier to cast as a pulling spell....<P>You use a bit more mana, but the mob is taking disease dot, poison dot, and your melee damage all at once.....<P>Tegulan
</FONT>
