<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
The shaman can solo at all levels and decently, even though not as well as some classes at all of those levels. (Necro's, Mages, and Droooids come to mind.)<P>It is a relatively easy concept for Shaman to solo. Here are the basic steps that are the same up through the levels. Fudge them as you will for your own personal style.<P>1 - Slow (Great line of spells)<BR>2 - Poison DoT<BR>3 - Disease DoT<BR>4 - Root<BR>5 - Back up and Meditate while MoB dies.<BR>6 - Reapply Poison and Root as needed.<BR>7 - Melee/DD to finish up<P>That is it in a nut shell. Sure some Shaman had Warriors as their first character and thus like to melee more than others. So they would not bother with rooting most of the time, just smack the beastie down while the DoT's do their business. Other shaman played weenie casters for too many levels and will run around in circles "kiting" their foes. Each to their own style I guess.<P>I love my Shaman Tank. (Sherman Tank) We have decent enough AC. Close to the rangers/rogues in both AC and HP's though our melee abilities and weaponry is no where near either any 'melee' class. We make up for that with our spell selection. Haste self and slow mobs suddenly makes us into a far better melee class. Toss in a pet and some DoT's and we are a force for solo'ing in a melee style. Did I mention I LOVE my Shaman Tank?<P>In addition, here is just a little something of what you are looking forward to as a shaman in a group situation as well.<P>Keyword : Versatility.<P>Subtle differences in what, as a shaman, I had as a role. But it is the ability to shift roles as the group dynamics change that makes us such a wanted class. Sure we really do not have much in the way of a class defining ability ( Alchemy aside ) which no other class is able to do. But we are the oil that keeps the group working smoothly. We flow into the cracks, filling almost any need the group may have. <P>Last night in 4 groups of various make-ups, I played 4 slightly different roles. Listed are the roles in order of importance for the group.<P>First group in SolB's LBugs consisted of a cleric/monk/ranger/warrior/druid, I was Slow/Haste/Buffer.<P>Second group in King consisted of cleric/monk/ranger/warrior/enchanter, I was Slow/Heal/Buffer. Most of the heals were of the enchanter as she got bounced around mez'ing.<P>In the third group in Tiger consisting of a pally/druid/enchanter, I was Slow/Healer/Melee/Buffer.<P>Fourth group in Tiger was Druid/Enchanter, I was Tank/Slow/DoT/Buffer. This was nearly a solo'ing type situation.<P>--------------------<P>~I'm a little teapot, short and stout. Here is my handle. Here is my spout. Tip me over and pour me out.~ Ancient Halfling Warrior Chant<P>Failbhean, 51 Champion<BR>Failbhe, 52 Mystic
</FONT>
