Our DoTs can also break root (since they have a DD component), but it happens far less frequently than a pure DD spell.<P>I usually drop on a Tainted Breath and Envenomed Breath (Yes, they do stack despite what some people claim), then Root and back off to med/heal/Cannibalize (only if I am above 80% health and my regen is doing fine to cover any damage I take).  Most of the time the DoTs drop off before Root, so I get up and renew them, then renew Root when it breaks and repeat the process.<P>After two rounds of poison, most monsters are low enough that they are going to try to flee when Root breaks.  At that point I blast with a couple DDs and loot.  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">
