<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I remember when I was 34 in north karana, still pimping my full banded and bf hammer, I almost got smacked by an sg, but I used the following strategy: I trained the hg to guard tower, let him kill the 2 guards, after that he was at about 1/3 hps, and then I cast scourge, and ran around like a little girl for a good while, that's not feasible tho to get steady exp, I know, but at the level I was, I was so happy to get 30pp.<BR>In any case, I didn't solo much at all up until level 45, I didn't even know the true power of a shaman as I'd just dd, heal, buff all the time.<BR>But I still have soloing advice that might be of help, personally, I'd ditch the pet, they're weak, unless u want to summon one after every fight but that's a waste of mana.  As I still use my level 14 root, I'd still stick with that, casting time is lower and less mana.  I'd also put dex and cha buff up to make your spells more effective.  I don't know if dex does anything, maybe it's just luck that it works better when I choose to dex myself, but anyways...  Also make shure to have regen on and cannibalize memmed.  And say you wanna fight an sg or whatever, slow him first, root, dot, sit down at a distance, and just wait (enstill won't make a difference, I've found that mobs have an pretty much equal chance at breaking any root while dd'ed or dotted).  And once u see root break, stand up quick, root him, back up and sit again until dot wears off and recast, etc etc.  I'm figuring an sg has what, 1500 hps?  3-4 scourges should do the job, and while u sit down just watching him decay, u'll be regaining mana, and if he's slowed and manages to hit u before u get root off, shouldn't be too damaging.  It's a long fight, but at that level I think that's one of the better ways to solo as a shaman, and it's not very good at that either because we don't get snare.  You can envy the druids all you won't, but if you hang in there, you'll get your reward in due time.  How many other classes other than shamans are capable of soloing level 51+ mobs?  At level 51 u get one of the best spells in the game, and it slows a mob's attack rate by 75%, which make them beasts.  Oh, and another advantage compared to druids, u can farm dungeons much easier where the good stuff drops, I remember spending one week clearing everything around solo, and got 20 level 39 summon corpse spells and 3 ishva robes that I lottoed with me, myself and I  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">  So yah, all in all, I'd recommend getting into good groups up until high 40s, shamans are not really designed to solo at lower levels, but once u get there, you can start cruisin 5th gear and rise above almost any other class when it comes to solo capabilities. Regrowth/stat buffs/chloroblast/cannibalize III/turgurs/jbb/root/dots u can't really beat that combo :-)   <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P>Nektar Nefaste, 59 shaman
