Sorry to say, but post 50, u can pretty much forget about melee cuz there's no way even if u had 3000 ac that u could absorb double hits of 120-200dmg considering at my level, I have 1200ish base hps unbuffed.  <BR>Reason why shaman pets are useless?  A shaman is not designed to be an outdoor kiter, he shines the most in dungeons where other classes would be crushed in 2 seconds.  Pets in a dungeon, extremly bad idea, for one, he's green, so his and consequently your aggro range is considerably larger, and for another when the mob starts running away he would just cause trains and in a dungeon, very bad idea to put a pet on /notaunt cuz at least if u see the message taunting attacker master and he's nowhere in sight, it's a pretty safe bet to either zone or gate the hell out.  <BR>Up until level 45, I didn't even know what slowing was, I was always grping outdoors, and I'd just heal/buff/melee with my UB0R bf hammer, so I know what the hard way is, although I only maxed 2hb.  However, it's not true that u cannot max your other melee skillz at higher levels, I'm just too lazy to practice piercing on blues during raids for instance, but no matter what level you are, if a shaman slows all the time, you're BOUND to max your defense cuz slow = aggro, aggro = mob on you, mob on you = sometimes he misses u = defense skill automatically goes up.  The only melee skill I regret not practicing is piercing but if I was adamant on maxing it, I could just swing at blue-yellow-red mobs all day during a guild raid.  AC is a key aspect to his survival, but wisdom is crucial to him more than u might think and eventually u will realize my point.  It's like telling a level 55 warrior to solo drolvarg captain in that case, the tank is gunna get SMOKED without a doubt whilst a shaman is perfectly capable of doing so with slows/malosi/cannibalize/heals/dots (shaman dds at high levels are rendered useless because of casting time), the best solution is to try and balance out wisdom and ac at the same time, wisdom being given priority to a certain degree.  I often camp sentient in wakening, double hit for 117 and kicks for 50ish, don't tell me ac is gunna be the determining factor in your success, u need fire power to take down something with 7-8k hps, and without the mana power, u can pride yourself in your ac and melee skillz all u want, but u will go down in a heartbeat with mana being depleted so rapidly.  AC helps, it helps a LOT, but above all, your mana is what counts the most (to a certain extent of course).<P>--------------------<P>Nektar Nefaste, 59 shaman
