Well, that's the very POINT of having high AC, Somadjinn. The higher your AC the less you get hit and the less likely you are to get hit for max damage. I have just short of 1800 hitpoints self buffed at 56 and I can stand head to head with dars and boks in Sebilis, solo, long enough that Plague wears off before they die pretty often. The boks beat on me pretty hard still, sometimes I have to toss a heal on myself during the fight, but dars rarely knock a bubble of health off me.<P>I'm still surprised so many people repeat this misinformation over and over again about teh shaman class and melee. It's not that hard to verify or disprove. Assuming you have good AC gear and max defense skill, suit up and go try it. I don't know about YOUR shaman, but my shaman can stand against a slowed Sebilis bok longer than most warriors my level can against an un-slowed Sebilis bok. That's not an un-impressive capabilty.
