<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Speaking from the standpoint of a measily lev 26, I can appreciate the value of AC....I recently went from a 2hb to a piercer/shield combo (+6 wis +15 ac) and saw a rather significant improvement in my remaining HPs after battle.  And, of course, the Jade Chok Prod gave me extra wisdom so it was a win/win solution over my old glowing wooden crook.  As far as mana pool regen is concerned, you can argue it any way you want, but a higher wisdom pool keeps you active for longer periods of time than a smaller pool.  Even if the mana pool is measured on a percent basis I might be draining only 25% with a kill while the other guy is draining 50%....who's up and ready for battle faster?  And regen/cannabilize is not the solution to make that gap up unless you have a bunch more hit points.
</FONT>
