Slam, your point on total mana pool is well taken on uber-mob raids where you start the fight with full mana - but not in the average grind group. I can't remember the last time I was full mana in a grind group. I usually try to keep between two and three bubbles of mana all the time, which I do by canning between fights. Having more total mana won't make me mana regen faster, or cannibalize faster either. But having high AC will likely leave me with more health to convert after the fight.
