<BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>AC is a key aspect to his survival  <HR></BLOCKQUOTE><BR>Did I not say ac was important?  Yes, I did, but I wouldn't strive to get 1k ac at the expense of 60 wisdom either, at lower levels, doesn't matter as much, but have u ever been in OS when the tank pulls 5 mobs at once?  What does a shaman do?  Turgur a couple, pump in some heals to the puller while the cleric is trying the same, and resume to slowing the other ones, and I've often found myself at 20 mana after the whole ordeal is over, including the fact that slows sometimes are resisted and will not land unless the mob is tashed/malosinied, if u have 140 wisdom let's say, in a lot of situations the grp will NOT survive because a mob unslowed at higher levels deal too much dmg, it's nice and dandy to have high ac, but if u don't have the proper amt mana to slow everything around, you're as good as dead.  AC really helps, but considering so much is demanded out of a shaman spellwise, you do need quite a lot of mana to keep the grp alive, and u saying that u can tank a slowed mob more efficiently than a warrior when unslowed just proves my point, if you're oom, you're oom, simple as that and no matter what your ac is, you will drop like a bowling pin if the mob is not slowed.  What you need is a good combination of wisdom/ac, and remember, chanters have poor ac, and how do they survive with all that aggro?  <BR>With good wisdom and mediocre ac, you can  survive ok, with terrible wisdom and excellent ac, good luck.<BR>I have about 860 ac and 1700 hps buffed, and 200 wisdom with bearform (not necessary, 180 wisdom could probably get u just as far), and I do just fine except for times like today in Hate when the puller aggroed 3 clerics of innoruuk, a kirakuwhatever, and an ire ghast, with 3 clerics beating on me like mad unslowed, u think it will make a difference if I had 140 more ac in hopeless situations like those when almost everyone around is dead?  Maybe a couple seconds, but that would just add to the tension   Now time to log back on, and await my rez to re-earn my 57th level   <IMG SRC="tongue.gif" border="0">   <IMG SRC="redface.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P>Nektar Nefaste, 59 shaman
