<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Somadjinn, you're right in pointing out about mana regen being different from absolute mana total, of course.  No matter what your mana level, if you cast a spell, it takes the same amount of time to med the mana back. Slamdunkjam, if I cast three spells that cost me 500 mana, say, and I have twice the wisdom of somebody else, we both med/canni the mana back in the same time.  It's just that I can do twice what he can only do once; that has no effect on how fast I get the mana back for any spell I actually cast, though.<P>Somadjinn, I've spoken to some post-50's shamans who tell me they melee a lot post-50.  I'm sure they can't do it on many mobs, and can do it on many others.  At least, that's what they've told me.  You do say that shamans can't solo efficiently until 49, then say they can't melee after 50.  That doesn't match what I've experienced before 49, or what some shamans I know have experienced after 50.  <P>Shamy, you're my melee hero.   <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">  I'd love to be able to melee stuff at your level!  There's no kind of option I don't like, and anyway it sounds like seriously fun butt-kicking, and something to look forward to. <P>I think a high level like you still working up melee skills is definitely doing it the hardest way, though, and having a fungi tunic, epic spear, and the kind of gear a level 60 has, sure must help.  Having gone through it myself, I'm glad I just got most of it over with when it was easier and took less gear, less danger, and less overall power.  I think most people will find that the earlier they start, the better -- and the earlier the pay-off, the long they have to enjoy it.
</FONT>
