Right, Blarg, I see what your saying.  The key in your scenario is that you have twice the wisdom.  Last nite in LoIO, I took on a sabertooth that conned formidable blue to me.  I was able to take him out with a combo of nukes, dots and melee.  While I was on my way to the windmill to med, I came across a high blue skelly.  In the past I wouldn't have taken him on.  But, my health was high from the last battle and still had over 50% mana left so I took him on and killed it.  I never would have been able to do that with my previous character.  The key was wisdom.....I was up and active instead of regening/canning cause my 139 wis permitted me to.  It didn't hurt, of course, to have a 15 ac shield and jaundiced boned and totemic armor also.
