<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Since level 40, I've had no melee weapons whatsoever (finally gave up my bf hammer lol), just my paw of opolla and testament of vanear (which I destroyed 2 days ago :eek <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">, and I've maxed my defense a VERY long time ago, and why?  Because slows almost instantaneuously cause aggro as a good shaman will try to cast it on the mobs asap (considering they're not too mr which is the case in the typical situation, but in any case, u could always malosi/malosini which causes practically no aggro and then slow), your defense will AUTOMATICALLY go up, and for a shaman, I'd say the most crucial skill needed is defense, and no melee weapons whatsoever are needed to raise it.  <BR>I've been thinking about it, and some offensive skillz can prove to be useful in some cases, not because of the pure dmg output, but because of procs, I regret that my piercing is still relatively low (60ish) because I hardly ever get the chance to land a stun with my howling harpoon, but it's just a matter of pure laziness too, catching up is the same as building your skill progressively, except that you'll have so many pts to catch all at once, but that's ok, as long as the mob is blue con and above, u can still get improvements, and at level 57 I've seen from the times I've tried gettings imps is not slow, I just get discouraged of having to catch up 140 points one day, and generally stop.<BR>I'll digress a little and explain as to why shamans can be cool and just sponge up the exp sometimes, of course, this is just my theory, but that's what I have been applying in most cases.  A shaman is basically made to slow (and maybe debuff their mr if the situation so calls for a malosi), any buffs they want, they ask for, and don't expect me to guess what stats of theirs are maxed.  On normal pulls with clarity II, I almost always have fm after the fight is over because all I do really is slow at the beginning of a fight, stay up for a while and just cannibalize for mana because I know if I sit down the mob will jump on me instaneously, and after tanks have taunted the mob sufficiently, I just sit down, and so on and so forth with next pulls, but when the tank pulls a nasty train, who do you think is gunna help keeping the group alive when I'm at full mana to start with?  I'll have sufficient enough mana to slow 6 of them and throw in a few chloroblasts to help the cleric out in the beginning where u have the most chances of dying.  That's my philosophy on how shamans should play, everyone in their grp is assigned one specific task or 2, and if everyone gets their **** together, there's no need for the shaman to waste extra mana healing/dotting/nuking, I follow the better to be safe than sorry principle, that is letting the tanks simply melee the mob when there's a single/double pull, and when worst comes to worst, I know the grp can rely on me to have enough mana to deal with 6+ slows in one sweep.  In the case of single/double pulls, that's when I could start practicing my offensive skills because I normally regen my mana to full before they even get the mob to half, but I'm just lazy, and sometimes just sit down or just chain JBB :-)<P>--------------------<P>Nektar Nefaste, 59 shaman
