<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Thanks for the great replies, guys.<P>I know you guys can work up defense without going the solo/heavy melee route, but getting hit a few times per mob when grouped doesn't seem to add up to the kind of volume of hits you sustain when you're soloing something and meleeing it, even if your group pulls quickly.  When I melee/solo, my fights last a couple of minutes, and I get hit sometimes many dozens of times every fight.  Even doing it that way, I often found it hard to catch up on defense, going for hours and hours without a single point increase.  I think grouping a lot will level you faster, but you won't be able to put on defense as fast as someone doing the melee/solo thing.  It just takes too long to get skill increases.  I don't need a mob hitting my tanks, I need to be the tank!  Now that I've maxed out defense/offense, though, I don't have to care any more, really.  My weapons I can max pretty much when I feel like it, I figure; they're behind, but not much now.  I AM glad I got the extra AC now rather than later though.  I never got hit enough in groups to come close to maxing out defense, offense, or weapons per level.<P>One nice thing about weapons skills being high, also, is that I land so often I proc very frequently.  I've often proc'd four Blight Hammer 533 dots in a battle, or four DD's from my drakkell icegrinder, or even six stuns from my howling harpoon.  Wonder how many times I could stun with the 6/23 mortificator spear -- that guy is darn fast.  Probably won't save anyone's life in a group if I'm doing it, but it's very nice to get maximum value from the melee I do contribute.<BR>___________________<BR>Chain JBB sure sounds great.  Only seen one JBB being sold ever, though, in the year and a half I've been playing.  Lotta people seem to have them, but I hear the drop rate has been nerfed.  <IMG SRC="frown.gif" border="0"> Ack, if it's even worse than it has been, I can't imagine how I'm ever gonna get one.  They're just not sold on Drinal, my server, it seems.  <IMG SRC="frown.gif" border="0">  If I get one at all, I'll probably be very, very high level by then.<P>Maybe I should just save up for a strathbone shield instead.  Only seen one of those sold, too, though.  <P>Hell, maybe I'll blow my money on alchemy and stop thinking about it heheh.
